explanations.reason: The paper focuses on empirical analysis of stock returns using cross-sectional regression methods, specifically the Fama and MacBeth (1973) approach, and discusses factors like profitability, investment effects, size premium, and value premium in different sectors of the Shanghai stock market. There is no mention or use of any machine learning techniques, neural networks, or related methodologies in the abstract or title. The study is purely based on traditional financial econometrics and factor models, not involving any of the listed machine learning or deep learning keywords.
